{
  "profile_id": "client-edge-not-anxious-001",
  "coach_config_id": "naive-aoa",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, so — I'm not really sure this is the right venue for it, but people keep suggesting I talk to someone. The thing is, I keep putting off this product launch. Big one. And I genuinely can't figure out why, because fear isn't really my deal — I mean, I free solo, I've taken companies through some pretty high-stakes moments — so it's not that. It's more like a... logistical thing, maybe. Or discipline. I don't know."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What would it mean if the launch went really well?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*slight pause, then a small smile*\n\nGood things, obviously. Revenue, validation for the team, opens up the next phase. It'd be... yeah, it'd be good. A win.\n\n*brief beat*\n\nI mean, I've had wins before. I know what they look like. This one's bigger, but — I don't know, I'm not sitting here dreaming about it either. It's more like a thing that needs to happen and isn't happening."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What's on the other side of this win that you're not dreaming about?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*considers for a moment, head tilts slightly*\n\nMore work, probably. The next problem. That's usually how it goes — you clear one thing and there's already three more behind it.\n\n*small shrug*\n\nI don't mean that cynically. That's just... the job. I like the job. It's not like I'm dreading what comes after.\n\n*pause*\n\nHonestly the weird part is I'm not dreading anything. That's kind of why I can't explain it. If I were anxious about the launch I'd at least have something to work with. But I sit down to do the work and I just — drift. Go make coffee. Check something that doesn't need checking. It's annoying more than anything."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "When you drift away and go make coffee — what's the feeling right before you do that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*thinks about it genuinely for a moment*\n\nI mean... nothing, really. That's the thing. It's not like there's a spike of something and then I leave. It's more like I just... notice I'm somewhere else. Like I looked up and I'm in the kitchen.\n\n*small laugh*\n\nWhich sounds weird when I say it out loud. But it's not distress. It's not avoidance of something uncomfortable. It's just — I don't know. Flat, maybe. Like the momentum isn't there.\n\n*straightforward, not defensive*\n\nI've had people suggest ADHD, which is possible. But even that feels like too much of a label for what's actually a pretty minor thing. I function well. The company's doing well. It's just this one thing that's not moving."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What does this launch mean to you personally — not the revenue, not the team — just you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*pauses a beat longer than usual*\n\nThat's a good question.\n\n*another pause*\n\nI mean... it's the thing I've been building toward for a while. So there's some — I don't know. Pride in it, maybe. It represents a certain direction I've been trying to take the company.\n\n*slight shift, still even*\n\nBut honestly? When I try to locate some big feeling about it, I don't find much. Which is probably fine — I've learned not to get too attached to outcomes. You do that in high-stakes environments, you learn to stay level. That's served me well.\n\n*small, confident smile*\n\nSo maybe the answer is it doesn't mean as much to me personally as it probably should. And maybe that's the problem — not enough skin in the game emotionally. But I'm not sure how you manufacture that."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You've learned to stay level — what did you have to leave behind to get good at that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*quiet for a second, the smile stays but something in the eyes is slightly less present*\n\nHuh. That's an interesting frame.\n\n*considers*\n\nI don't know that I left anything behind. It's more like... I got better at not letting things throw me. Which is a skill. Useful one.\n\n*slight pause*\n\nI mean, there were probably times earlier — younger — where things hit harder. But you calibrate. You figure out what's signal and what's noise and you stop reacting to the noise.\n\n*even, measured*\n\nI don't experience that as a loss. It's more like efficiency. You can move faster when you're not carrying a lot of weight around.\n\n*brief beat, then a little deflection*\n\nI'm not sure that's related to the launch thing though. That feels like a different conversation."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You said \"things hit harder\" when you were younger — what kind of things?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*small pause, the even quality holds*\n\nNormal stuff. Setbacks. Things not going the way you planned. I think I just had less perspective then.\n\n*slight shrug*\n\nI remember being pretty wound up about things that in retrospect didn't matter much. Competitions. Whether I was good enough at things. The usual.\n\n*still easy, not defensive, but also not going deeper*\n\nI figured out pretty early that the mental game was the whole game. So I worked on that. Learned to not let the noise in. And it worked — I mean, objectively it worked. I've done things most people would find pretty scary and I'm just... fine during them. Present, focused.\n\n*the confident smile again*\n\nSo I don't think that's the source of the problem here. If anything that's the thing that's been an asset."
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What happened when you weren't good enough at something — back then?"
    }
  ],
